dden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">0.5</code> means the learning rate decays from p=
eak to 50% of peak using cosine annealing. Classification uses minimal warm=
up (<code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-x=
s font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/3=
0">20</code> steps) while detection uses more warmup (<code class=3D"rounde=
d-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15=
px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">100</code> steps) to s=
tabilize training of the randomly-initialized DETR head.</p>
